  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To observe the desirable role of argumentation in an example of dangerous human use of artificial agents engineered in the absence of logicist formalisms and techniques, we can consider the logic-less \"large language model\" Galactica, engineered and released by its creators in order to provide human beings with \"a new interface for science\" (Taylor et al., 2021), at least seemingly a rather laudable goal for human-centric AI.",
    "As a matter of fact, Galactica, with minimal prompts from a human, can quickly write entire scientific papers, replete with references.",
    "It does this by way of deep learning only.",
    "Unfortunately, when used by some human scientists, Galactica simply concocted many things having no relation to relevant reality.",
    "For instance, some of the references in scientific papers it \"wrote\" were completely fictional but of course sounded quite legitimate."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To observe the desirable role of argumentation in an example of dangerous human use of artificial agents engineered in the absence of logicist formalisms and techniques, we can consider the logic-less \"large language model\" Galactica, engineered and released by its creators in order to provide human beings with \"a new interface for science\" (Taylor et al., 2021), at least seemingly a rather laudable goal for human-centric AI."
  ]
